"{\"uid\": \"slate.com-culture-2024-07-olympics-paris-seine-sewage-triathlon-e-coli-safe-swimming.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This is part of Slate's 2024 Olympics coverage.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 47, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.869083760835954e-44, \"text\": \"Slate\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read morehere.\", \"from\": 48, \"to\": 62, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are enjoying our coverage from Paris, joinSlate Plusto support our work.\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 142, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They swam in the damn Seine.\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 166, \"end\": 171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 8 a.m. Wednesday, 55 women dove in under a heavy gray sky.\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The city was quiet except for the buzzing of the helicopters overhead, and spectators with binoculars roamed the bridges and thequaisalongside curious commuters.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the swimmers came downstream, they moved in a tight splashing pack like fish jumping or rapids for the race helpers in their kayaks.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But as they turned to cross the river, then upstream, the separation began: Now they were swimming against a powerful current running at just under a meter a second.\", \"from\": 533, \"to\": 698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It felt like a treadmill.\", \"from\": 699, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The water tests came in at 3:20 a.m. Wednesday.\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Triathlon, the city and regional government, and the French weather serviceconvened, for the fourth day in a row, at 3:30 a.m.  And the flagship promise of the 2024 Paris Games-swimming competitions in a restored Seine, in the shadow of the Eiffel Tower-came true at the unholy hour of4:14 a.m., less than four hours before the women's triathlon race began.\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.539247198696265e-18, \"text\": \"World Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Triathlon\"}, {\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9994117341142146, \"rank\": 0.0005528144626764889, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's an hour not known for sound decisionmaking, and critics have alleged a sudden lack of transparency from officials about water quality.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After two months of weekly reports from the city of Paris, the Paris 2024 Olympics organizers havestopped publishing data.\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1401, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But right at 8 a.m., as the women took their places on the platform beneath the gilded statues of the Pont Alexandre III, the debate stopped and the sport began.\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1505, \"end\": 1523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont Alexandre III\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Alexandre_III\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe, between the river that was too dirty to practice in, the slippery cobblestones of the Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es under their wheels, and crowds cheering the run through Paris, there was a kind of home-field advantage: Just under two hours later, the French triathlete Cassandre Beaugrand brought home the gold.\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728108773, \"rank\": 0.005341849563966386, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}, {\"begin\": 1729, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9994117341142146, \"rank\": 0.0005528144626764889, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1828, \"end\": 1847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cassandre Beaugrand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a $1.6 billion decadelong campaign to make the Seine safe for swimming, bad weather nearly scuttled the whole thing.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Half a month's worth of rain fell Friday and Saturday, forcing officials to cancel race practices and postpone the men's race by a day.\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All this after officials, most prominently Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo, had bet their reputations on a clean river (to the extent that a Hidalgo stand-in in the French Netflix smashUnder Parisinsists on holding a triathlon in the river despite the presence of a mammoth shark).\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 2291, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9994117341142146, \"rank\": 0.0005528144626764889, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To understand how the city's most high-profile Olympian pledge nearly turned into a big embarrassment, you have to go right to the smelly source of the problem: the sewers.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 1.925003692413333e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cleaning up the Seine is a bit of a misnomer.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's not an issue of industrial pollution, and it's not about trash,\\\" Pauline Lavaud, an adviser to the mayor, said on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999999982119334, \"rank\": 1.7880080593474384e-09, \"text\": \"Pauline\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This question of 'Are we really going to be able to swim in the Seine?'\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2822, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"is tied to the idea that there is everything and anything down there and we have to clean it out.\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But even if there are a fewV\\u00e9libdown there, that's not the issue.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 2993, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The issue is the bacteria.\\\"\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the bacteria come from toilets, which join showers, sinks, and rainfall in the sewers.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The toilets are reliable; the rainfall, increasingly, is not, and causes overflow into the river.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sewer engineer's riddle: What do you get when you mix a gallon of sewage with a gallon of rainfall?\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two gallons of sewage.\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of the Parisian sewer system dates from the middle of the 19thcentury, when Napoleon III embarked on his urban renewal campaign.\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3421, \"end\": 3429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1841909140721834e-65, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The most famous of those Paris projects were Haussmann's boulevards, but they came with an underground parallel: a system of sewers with blue-white-and-green signs to match the ones above, all tall enough for a man to stand in.\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3499, \"end\": 3504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8560648071230328e-55, \"text\": \"Haussmann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, most men-it was a bit tight for Paris Deputy Mayor Antoine Guillou, the towering 35-year-old in charge of the city's sanitation system.\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3741, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday morning, he joined a group of reporters in the city's sewer museum with a difficult assignment: explaining how Paris had made the Seine clean enough to swim in.\", \"from\": 3845, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3966, \"end\": 3971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3985, \"end\": 3990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though, at that moment, it was not yet clean enough to swim in.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4084, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us digress briefly on the existence of a sewer museum, legacy of a rich Paris tradition of sewer tourism.\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4162, \"end\": 4167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eug\\u00e8ne Belgrand, the father of the system and author of a five-volume sewer text sprinkled with Latin quotations, boasted, \\\"No foreign sovereign, no important personage, left Paris without having visited the collectors.\\\"\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4203, \"end\": 4211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\", \"score\": 0.9529505816115332, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Belgrand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e8ne_Belgrand\"}, {\"begin\": 4292, \"end\": 4297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4206033263161243e-15, \"text\": \"Latin\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}, {\"begin\": 4371, \"end\": 4376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Czar Alexander II and King Wilhelm I were among the visitors; there were sewer trains for visitors and boats with cushioned seats.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the musty barnyard smell of the brown rivers-rivulets, creeks, the roaring flow of the main Left Bank channel-seemed less unusual in that stinking 19th-century world.\", \"from\": 4548, \"to\": 4722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4648, \"end\": 4657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.311415502711904e-20, \"text\": \"Left Bank\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rive_Gauche\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris was also proud of its sewers, which had drained the muddy, fetid mess of the Second Empire's streets.\", \"from\": 4724, \"to\": 4835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4728, \"end\": 4733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first sewers were built just for rainwater.\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, after much debate, it was decided that they should also be connected to household waste.\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Haussmann did not want disgusting fecal matter in the underground galleries; the night-soil industry wanted its fertilizer profits.\", \"from\": 4980, \"to\": 5111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4980, \"end\": 4989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8560648071230328e-55, \"text\": \"Haussmann\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haussmann's_renovation_of_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Landlords did not want to pay for the connections to replace their cesspools, stinking pits that in addition to their evident health risks led most building owners to discourage fresh-water use inside buildings, lest the cesspool fill too quickly.\", \"from\": 5112, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Public health prevailed, but with a major consequence: Like most older cities, Paris wound up with a \\\"combined sewer system\\\" of rainwater and sewage.\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5440, \"end\": 5445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When there is too much rainwater for the system, the emergency valves tip it all into the Seine, a safety net for the city.\", \"from\": 5511, \"to\": 5634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5601, \"end\": 5606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Also, the sewer museum closes for high water about four days a year.)\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The billion-dollar cleanup, Guillou said, has come in three parts.\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First, the city made sure that all the region's informal housing-and especially the Bateaux Mouches and other riverboats-was connected to the sewer system.\", \"from\": 5775, \"to\": 5930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, water treatment plants were improved to filter and clean wastewater before feeding it back into the river.\", \"from\": 5932, \"to\": 6046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Third, the city built what Guillou calls \\\"the underground cathedral of Paris,\\\" a storage tank at Austerlitz, on the city's east side, capable of holding 55,000 cubic meters of wastewater during storms like the one on Friday.\", \"from\": 6048, \"to\": 6272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6119, \"end\": 6124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6145, \"end\": 6155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9998502402851402, \"rank\": 0.00014978214640433128, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a Parisian version of a \\\"deep tunnel,\\\" the kind of massive underground wastewater storage containers that have been constructed in Chicago, Washington, and other U.S. cities to comply with the Clean Water Act.\", \"from\": 6273, \"to\": 6487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6409, \"end\": 6416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9509968333056706e-21, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 6418, \"end\": 6428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.5770154839214487e-11, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since the basin came online in May, Paris has not dumped any wastewater into the Seine.\", \"from\": 6488, \"to\": 6575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6524, \"end\": 6529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6569, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately for the triathletes, the Seine does not begin in Paris.\", \"from\": 6577, \"to\": 6646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6616, \"end\": 6621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 6640, \"end\": 6645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The current water-quality problems are the fault of communities upstream, officials say, exacerbated by the fact the river is currently flowing at four times its normal summer speed after a record-breaking rainy spring.\", \"from\": 6647, \"to\": 6866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The watershed that contributes to Parisian water quality has effectively grown.\", \"from\": 6867, \"to\": 6946, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For Olympics organizers, athletes, international media, and the city of Paris, the occurrence of Wednesday's triathlons seemed to be a judgment on the success or failure of cleaning the Seine.\", \"from\": 6948, \"to\": 7140, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7020, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3434318109288112e-37, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7134, \"end\": 7139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that gets it backward.\", \"from\": 7141, \"to\": 7167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics may have motivated the region to get its act together, but the real achievement is restoring the river-not for a specific day but in general.\", \"from\": 7168, \"to\": 7322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There were just three species of fish in the Seine when Mayor Jacques Chirac promised that it would one day be swimmable; now there are 36.\", \"from\": 7323, \"to\": 7462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7368, \"end\": 7373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 7385, \"end\": 7399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Chirac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next summer, three free public pools will open in the city; two dozen communities in the suburbs have asked to do the same.\", \"from\": 7464, \"to\": 7587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be days when you can not swim, like Monday, but during a typical dry Parisian summer, there will be many more days when you can.\", \"from\": 7588, \"to\": 7727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a return, of sorts, to a time when Parisians bathed in the Seine by the thousands.\", \"from\": 7728, \"to\": 7816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7793, \"end\": 7798, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That has been illegal for more than 100 years.\", \"from\": 7817, \"to\": 7863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, that will do little to assuage the irritation of competitors and spectators.\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With an 18-hour delay between sampling and results and lots of rain on Wednesday morning, we may never get an official water-quality reading from the morning of the race.\", \"from\": 7953, \"to\": 8123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One company that performs independent water samplessuggested, \\\"We are in a complex situation,\\\" with differing indicators from different tests on Tuesday night, but concluded: \\\"Today, the Seine has a significant presence of particle-bound E.coli.\\\"\", \"from\": 8124, \"to\": 8370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8311, \"end\": 8316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At leastone swimmer saidit did not taste good.\", \"from\": 8371, \"to\": 8417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If the priority is the health of the athletes,\\\" the Belgian Marten Van Riel wrote on Instagram, \\\"this course would have been moved to another place a long time ago.\", \"from\": 8419, \"to\": 8584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8472, \"end\": 8479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.8716949462899777, \"rank\": 0.1471903149793098, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 8480, \"end\": 8495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marten Van Riel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marten_Van_Riel\"}, {\"begin\": 8505, \"end\": 8514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0793756894554532e-34, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are just puppets.\\\"\", \"from\": 8585, \"to\": 8606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the eve of the race, I met Eloi Adjavon, a triathlete from Togo who was having lunch with friends and family at a pizza place near the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 8608, \"to\": 8762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8638, \"end\": 8642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eloi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.557543086491973e-26, \"text\": \"Eloi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eloi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eloi\"}, {\"begin\": 8670, \"end\": 8674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2632486140439815e-20, \"text\": \"Togo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\"}, {\"begin\": 8746, \"end\": 8761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.570917894157404e-24, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of the postponement, his friends had to leave town before he competed.\", \"from\": 8763, \"to\": 8841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not easy to rearrange flights and hotels at a moment's notice.\", \"from\": 8842, \"to\": 8904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But his partner, Cl\\u00e9mence Depoortere, offered another perspective.\", \"from\": 8906, \"to\": 8972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair met in film school in Brussels eight years ago, before Adjavon decided to devote himself to triathlons.\", \"from\": 8973, \"to\": 9085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9004, \"end\": 9012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\", \"score\": 0.9999999999727152, \"rank\": 2.6927926106852218e-11, \"text\": \"Brussels\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brussels\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is making a movie about his journey to the Olympics, where he carried the flag for Togo down the rainy Seine.\", \"from\": 9086, \"to\": 9199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9173, \"end\": 9177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2632486140439815e-20, \"text\": \"Togo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Togo\"}, {\"begin\": 9193, \"end\": 9198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.602255693597639e-42, \"text\": \